C Networking Work Sample – ARP Test Utility
Author: Thai Nguyen

Purpose:
This work sample demonstrates systems-level networking knowledge using the C programming language on Linux. The utility resolves MAC addresses for a given IPv4 address by interacting directly with Ethernet and ARP protocols. It queries the operating system ARP cache and, when necessary, constructs and transmits ARP request frames using raw sockets.

What This Demonstrates:
•	Layer 2 and Layer 3 interactions (Ethernet, ARP, IPv4)
•	Raw socket programming using PF_PACKET on Linux
•	Manual construction and parsing of Ethernet and ARP protocol headers
•	Network interface discovery, validation, and binding via IOCtl
•	Interaction with OS-level networking state (ARP cache query and insertion)
•	Network-operations awareness relevant to distributed and mission-critical systems

Context:
This sample is provided as a technical demonstration artifact and is not production code.
Diagnostic output is intentionally included to make protocol behavior, packet structure, and state transitions explicit for review.
